1 bunch baby broccoli
½ lemon
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet chicken breast strips
1 packet Roasted Potatoes with Garlic Herb Butter
1 packet Smokey Aioli
olive oil

• Trim baby broccoli. Slice lemon into wedges
• Heat a frying pan over medium-high heat
• Cook baby broccoli with a dash of water until tender, 5 mins
• Add spinach and a squeeze of lemon juice, then stir until wilted
• Transfer to a plate

• In a bowl, combine spice blendchicken and a drizzle of olive oil
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil
• Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-4 mins each side

• Pierce a few holes in potato packet
• Microwave until hot and steaming, 3 mins
• Plate up the chicken, greens and potatoes
• Serve with smokey aioli and remaining lemon wedges